<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
Epigyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Acusilas tongi sp. nov. A-C, F-H female paratype IZCAS-Ar 42505 D, E holotype A epigyne, ventral view B ibid., posterior view C ibid., anterior view D habitus, dorsal view E ibid., lateral view F ibid., dorsal view G ibid., ventral view H left leg I, prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A-C); 1 mm (D-H)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1072.73345.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/612403" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">2A-C</figureCitation>
): wider than long, with narrow rim anteriorly and laterally, concave anteriorly; posterior lip hooked (see arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Acusilas tongi sp. nov. A-C, F-H female paratype IZCAS-Ar 42505 D, E holotype A epigyne, ventral view B ibid., posterior view C ibid., anterior view D habitus, dorsal view E ibid., lateral view F ibid., dorsal view G ibid., ventral view H left leg I, prolateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A-C); 1 mm (D-H)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1072.73345.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/612403" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">2C</figureCitation>
); copulatory openings narrow, located posteriorly; copulatory ducts shorter than spermatheca; spermathecae oval.
</paragraph>
